#!/usr/bin/env python3
# grok-bitch — a safe, deterministic harness for handing grunt work to grok.
#
# Built so Claude Code can delegate well-specified, verifiable "bitch work" to
# grok (model: grok-build) without risking the high-rigor work Claude owns.
#
# The guarantee this tool provides does NOT depend on trusting grok. It is
# defense-in-depth, with a deterministic verify-and-revert layer that holds
# regardless of what the executor does:
#
#   Layer 1  OS sandbox   -- grok runs under Landlock (--sandbox strict/read-only):
#                            writes confined to the workspace + tmp, child network
#                            blocked. Hard kernel boundary for OUT-of-tree paths.
#   Layer 2  Tool fence   -- web/X/interactive tools disabled; --yolo so grok can
#                            never hang on a permission/question prompt.
#   Layer 3  Perm denies  -- destructive shell + protected-path edits denied at the
#                            permission layer (deny always wins). Friction, not proof.
#   Layer 4  Guard+revert -- protected paths are byte-snapshotted before the run and
#                            re-hashed after. ANY change -> the run FAILS and the
#                            paths are restored. This is the real guarantee for
#                            IN-tree protected paths (docs/core, canonical/, ...),
#                            which Landlock cannot protect (subpath of a writable tree).
#   Layer 5  Verify gate  -- an acceptance command (e.g. `make check`) must pass or
#                            the run is reported as rejected.
#   Layer 6  Hard timeout -- wall-clock kill of grok and all its children.
#
# Single file, stdlib only. See README.md and AGENTS-GROK-BITCH.md.

