# IMPORTANT (learned the hard way): grok's OS sandbox is applied via Landlock,
# but only ENGAGES when grok has a controlling terminal (else it logs
# ApplyFailed and runs UNCONFINED). The harness gives grok a pty so the sandbox
# actually takes effect.
#
# Of grok's built-in profiles, only `workspace` is usable here: it confines
# WRITES to the workspace (+tmp/+~/.grok) via Landlock while leaving network up.
